<!DOCTYPE html>
<html>
<head>
  <title>HW5 in the CRUD</title>
  <%= stylesheet_link_tag    'application', media: 'all', 'data-turbolinks-track' => true %>
  <%= javascript_include_tag 'application', 'data-turbolinks-track' => true %>
  <%= csrf_meta_tags %>
</head>
<body>

<div>
	<ul>
		<li>
			<%= link_to "Home Index", home_path %>
		</li>
		<li>
			<%= link_to "User Index", users_path %>
		</li>
		<li>
			<%= link_to "All Posts", :all_posts %>
		</li>
	</ul>
</div>

<h1>HW5</h1>

<%= yield %>

<div>
	<ul>
		<li>
			<del>
				Create a new Rails app with a User model and a Post model.
			</del>
		</li>
		<li>
			Use model-based forms to create a basic CRUD functionality (Create, Read, Update, Destroy) for both users and posts.
		</li>
		<li>
			<del>
				A user should be able to sign up, login, and edit their profile.
			</del>
		</li>
		<li>
			Posts should be able to be created, seen, updated, and deleted
		</li>
	</ul>
</div>

</body>
</html>
